      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can we file a bug to remove `disable_android_thin_lto`?\n\nCurrently, `disable_android_thin_lto` is no-op because there is no other feature that implies `disable_android_thin_lto` and `disable_android_thin_lto` sets `enabled` to `False` by default. In other words, `not_features \u003d [\"disable_android_thin_lto]\"` is no-op here and other places.\n\nWe discussed offline and I learned that `disable_android_thin_lto` will be implied/enabled when `fuzzer` is implemented and enabled. We needed `disable_android_thin_lto` because it will expand `-fno-lto` flag. However, if `fuzzer` is the only factor that enable `disable_android_thin_lto`, we can have `fuzzer` to expand `-fno-lto` instead.\n\nRemoving `disable_android_thin_lto` reduces the code redirection and help reasoning about these features better.",
